<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="coming-badge">Coming 2026</div>
    <div class="hero-label">Habitat Residency</div>
    <h1>Live and build with<br><em>4 other founders</em><br>for 7 days.</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">You've already shipped an MVP. Now it's time to go deeper. Full immersion, dedicated mentorship, and a demo day in front of investors.</p>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span class="hero-meta-label">Duration</span>
        <span class="hero-meta-value">7 days</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span class="hero-meta-label">Cohort size</span>
        <span class="hero-meta-value">5 founders</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span class="hero-meta-label">Format</span>
        <span class="hero-meta-value">Live-in</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span class="hero-meta-label">Ends with</span>
        <span class="hero-meta-value">Demo day</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-buttons">
      <a href="contact.html?program=residency" class="btn-primary">Join the waitlist &rarr;</a>
      <a href="#what" class="btn-secondary">How it works</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHAT IS IT -->
<section id="what">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">What it is</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">From MVP to<br>business in a week.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">Habitat Residency is not a course. Not a coworking space. Not another accelerator. It's one week where you only build.</p>

    <div class="intro-grid fade-up">
      <div class="intro-text">
        <h3>The premise is simple.</h3>
        <p>Five founders, already past idea stage, live and work together for seven consecutive days. No commute. No context-switching. No meetings except the ones that matter.</p>
        <p>You get a dedicated mentor — a practitioner, not a professor — who works alongside you for the full week. You get access to a VC network for feedback and potential funding. And on day seven, you pitch.</p>
        <p>The goal isn't to raise money that week (though it happens). The goal is to leave knowing exactly where you're going and why.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="intro-stats">
        <div class="intro-stat">
          <div class="intro-stat-num">5</div>
          <div class="intro-stat-label">founders per cohort — small enough to build real trust</div>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-stat">
          <div class="intro-stat-num">7</div>
          <div class="intro-stat-label">consecutive days of focused, undistracted building</div>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-stat">
          <div class="intro-stat-num">1</div>
          <div class="intro-stat-label">dedicated mentor with you the entire week</div>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-stat">
          <div class="intro-stat-num">0</div>
          <div class="intro-stat-label">equity taken — ever</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE WEEK -->
<section class="week-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">The week</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Seven days, structured to ship.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">Each day has a clear theme. You're building the whole time — but we make sure you're building the right things in the right order.</p>

    <div class="week-grid">
      <div class="day-card fade-up">
        <div class="day-label">Day 1</div>
        <h3>Arrivals + alignment</h3>
        <p>Move in, meet your cohort, set your week goal. What does success look like by Friday? Get brutally honest about where you are.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="day-card fade-up">
        <div class="day-label">Day 2</div>
        <h3>Customer conversations</h3>
        <p>Your first full day is not building. It's talking to users. Structured interviews, real insights, kill your assumptions early.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="day-card fade-up">
        <div class="day-label">Day 3 — 4</div>
        <h3>Deep build</h3>
        <p>Two full days of heads-down work. Morning standups with your mentor. Afternoon unblocking sessions. Evening reviews with the cohort.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="day-card fade-up">
        <div class="day-label">Day 5</div>
        <h3>Test &amp; iterate</h3>
        <p>Get real users on your product. Run experiments. Fix what's broken. Stop adding features. Make what you have work better.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="day-card fade-up">
        <div class="day-label">Day 6</div>
        <h3>Story + pitch prep</h3>
        <p>What's your narrative? Why this, why now, why you? Practice your demo until the story is effortless.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="day-card fade-up">
        <div class="day-label">Day 7</div>
        <h3>Demo Day</h3>
        <p>Investors, mentors, and the broader Habitat community. 10-minute demo + Q&A. The beginning of the next chapter.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- MENTORSHIP -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">Support structure</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Not advice. Presence.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">The difference between a good program and a transformative one is whether the people helping you are actually in the room.</p>

    <div class="mentorship-grid">
      <div class="mentorship-card fade-up">
        <h3>Dedicated mentor</h3>
        <p>One practitioner — a founder, operator, or investor who has done what you're trying to do — works with your cohort the full week. Not for 2 hours. For the week.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mentorship-card fade-up">
        <h3>VC office hours</h3>
        <p>Investors from our network drop in for sessions throughout the week. Not to evaluate you — to help you think clearer. Evaluation happens at Demo Day, not before.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mentorship-card fade-up">
        <h3>Peer cohort</h3>
        <p>Four other founders at the same stage, with complementary skills, working alongside you. The cohort is small enough to build genuine trust — and honest enough to tell you hard truths.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
<section style="background: var(--cream);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">Who we select</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Already past zero.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">The Residency is for founders who've proven they can ship — and are ready to figure out whether they can build a business.</p>

    <div class="criteria-grid">
      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
        <h3>You've shipped an MVP</h3>
        <p>You have a live product — not a landing page, not a deck. Real code, real users, even if early. You know you can build.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
        <h3>You're pre or early revenue</h3>
        <p>You have some validation but you're not yet at scale. The Residency accelerates the period between "it works" and "it grows."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
        <h3>You can be all-in for a week</h3>
        <p>No day job meetings. No half-presence. Seven days of full focus. If you can't commit to that, the timing isn't right yet.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
        <h3>You want to be challenged</h3>
        <p>The cohort and mentor will push you. Good feedback is uncomfortable. You need to want that, not just tolerate it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- NOT FOR -->
<section class="not-for">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">Not for everyone</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Be honest with yourself.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">The Residency will make great founders better. It won't turn someone who isn't ready into a founder.</p>

    <div class="not-for-list fade-up">
      <div class="not-for-item">
        <div class="not-for-x">✕</div>
        <div class="not-for-text">You're still validating whether you want to be a founder</div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-for-item">
        <div class="not-for-x">✕</div>
        <div class="not-for-text">You haven't built or shipped anything yet</div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-for-item">
        <div class="not-for-x">✕</div>
        <div class="not-for-text">You're looking for co-founders (try our evenings first)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-for-item">
        <div class="not-for-x">✕</div>
        <div class="not-for-text">You can't step away from your current obligations for a week</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DEMO DAY -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">The culmination</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Demo Day.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">Day seven isn't a formality. It's the moment your week of work meets the people who can help you go further.</p>

    <div class="demo-day-content">
      <div class="demo-day-left fade-up">
        <p>Demo Day is a curated event open to investors from our network, the broader Habitat community, and select guests. Each founder has 10 minutes: a live product demo, not slides.</p>
        <p>Q&A follows. The conversation continues at the networking session after. Some founders leave with term sheets. Most leave with introductions, feedback, and a clearer path.</p>
        <p>All of them leave knowing exactly what the next 90 days look like.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-day-right fade-up">
        <div class="demo-day-feature">
          <div class="demo-day-feature-dot"></div>
          <div class="demo-day-feature-content">
            <h4>Live product demos only</h4>
            <p>No decks. No mockups. Your product, live, in front of people who matter.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="demo-day-feature">
          <div class="demo-day-feature-dot"></div>
          <div class="demo-day-feature-content">
            <h4>Curated investor audience</h4>
            <p>Early-stage VCs and angels from our network — people who write checks at this stage.</p>
          </div>
